## 4. The Hand Feel Experience

- Impact Sensation
    - Hardness Words: Crisp, solid, yet elastic (comes in 47.5° and 50° variants; both feel distinctly German).
    - Feedback: Clear and direct vibration transmission to the hand.
    - Hold vs. Release: A balanced catch and shoot feel. It holds the ball long enough to impart spin but releases it quickly for speed.
    - Dwell Time: Moderate. Longer than traditional speed-glue era rubbers, but shorter than pure Chinese tacky rubbers.

- Sound/Click
    - Produces a very satisfying, sharp metallic click on heavy impact, typical of high-end ESN tensors.

