## 5. Compatibility & Setup Guide

- Best Blade Matches
    - Outer Carbon: Great pairing for an ultra-aggressive, fast-paced attacking game (e.g., Viscaria style blades).
    - Inner Carbon: Excellent balance. The inner carbon tames the rubber's bounce in the short game while supporting its power away from the table.
    - All-Wood: Very good for developing players or those seeking maximum dwell time and control; pairs beautifully with 5-ply or 7-ply offensive blades.
    - Mismatch Cases: Extremely stiff, thick carbon blades (like Tamca 5000) might make the setup too uncontrollable and low-arc for amateur players.

- Forehand vs. Backhand Recommendation
    - Forehand: Excellent, especially in the 50° hardness, for players transitioning away from Chinese tacky rubbers who still want high spin but with more baseline speed.
    - Backhand: Highly recommended in the 47.5° hardness. It provides the crisp blocking, easy lifting, and punch power needed for modern backhand play.

